    <description><![CDATA[<h2 id="intro" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#intro" class="header-mark" aria-label="Header mark for 'Intro'"></a>Intro</h2><hr>
<p>The process of drawing a simple relation graph in python can be broken down into 2 steps.</p>
<ol>
<li>Define a graph.</li>
<li>Draw a graph.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="step-1-define-a-graph" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#step-1-define-a-graph" class="header-mark" aria-label="Header mark for 'Step 1. Define a graph'"></a>Step 1. Define a graph</h2><hr>
<p>In this step, we will use the <a href="https://networkx.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">networkx</a> package.</p>
<h3 id="install-tutorial" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#install-tutorial" class="header-mark" aria-label="Header mark for 'Install tutorial'"></a>Install tutorial</h3><p>If you are using conda, you can just type <code>conda install networkx</code></p>
<p>If you are using pip, you can just type <code>pip install networkx</code></p>]]></description>
